{"original_url": "https://www.skinnytaste.com/lentil-salad/", "credit_to": "SkinnyTaste", "author": "SkinnyTaste", "name": "Lentil salad", "prep_time": 15.0, "cook_time": 20.0, "ingredients": [{"ingred_name": "dry brown lentils", "amount": "1", "unit": "cup", "notes": "*"}, {"ingred_name": "bay leaf", "amount": "1", "unit": null, "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "sprigs fresh thyme", "amount": "2", "unit": null, "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "finely diced carrots", "amount": "1", "unit": "cup", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "finely diced celery", "amount": "1/3", "unit": "cup", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "finely diced red bell pepper", "amount": "1/4", "unit": "cup", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "finely diced red onion", "amount": "1/4", "unit": "cup", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "minced parsley", "amount": "1/4", "unit": "cup", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "garlic", "amount": "1", "unit": "clove", "notes": "minced"}, {"ingred_name": "lemon juice", "amount": "5", "unit": "tbsp", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "olive oil", "amount": "1", "unit": "tablespoon", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "kosher salt", "amount": "1", "unit": "teaspoon", "notes": null}, {"ingred_name": "fresh ground black pepper", "amount": null, "unit": null, "notes": null}], "instructions": "In a medium saucepan combine lentils, bay leaf, and thyme. Add enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer uncovered until lentils are tender but not mushy, about 16 to 20 minutes. Drain lentils and discard bay leaf and thyme. Place in a large work bowl with carrots, celery, red pepper, red onion, parsley, garlic, lemon juice, olive oil, salt and pepper. Toss to combine and serve chilled or room temperature."}